cs.DB, cs.DS, cs.DC, cs.CC, cs.LG. 

The paper deals with join algorithms, which are a fundamental aspect of database systems. Therefore, cs.DB (Databases) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves data structures and algorithms, which are covered by cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). The paper establishes worst-case optimality, which falls under cs.CC (Computational Complexity) and cs.LG (Machine Learning).
